==English==

===Alternative forms===
*to [[have another thing coming]] ''(only common form in US)''

===Expression===
'''[[to]] [[have]] [[another]] [[think]] [[coming]]'''  ''(mainly British)''

# To be deluded, to be mistaken.

====Usage notes====
*{{UK}}: This expression is used only in phrases of the form ''If X thinks that Y, he/she has another think coming!''  It is usually used in the present tense.  The form ''to have another thing coming'' is often seen, and arises from hearing the /k/ of ''think'' blended with the /k/ of ''coming'', making ''think'' sound like ''thing''.